        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(bedrock): enable prompt caching for Nova models",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #29707. Amazon Nova generation models on Bedrock were still treated as unsupported non-Anthropic models, so OpenClaw forced `cacheRetention: \"none\"` and never emitted Bedrock `cachePoint` blocks for Nova requests.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAWS documents explicit prompt caching support for Amazon Bedrock models, including Nova generation models: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/prompt-caching.html\n\nThis change teaches the shared Bedrock cache policy to recognize Nova Micro, Lite, Pro, Premier, and Nova 2 Lite refs, lets direct Nova requests keep their cache settings, and keeps the existing no-cache fallback for unsupported non-Anthropic Bedrock models. For Nova, `cacheRetention: \"long\"` emits the default Bedrock cache point without reusing Claude's `ttl: \"1h\"` field.\n\nThe follow-up commit also preserves configured direct Nova `cacheRetention` values through the normal agent extra-params path, including the explicit `cacheRetention: \"none\"` opt-out.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers can enable prompt caching for Bedrock Nova text models without hitting the previous runtime no-cache override. Unsupported non-Anthropic Bedrock models, such as Mistral, continue to be protected from unsupported cache metadata.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/prompt-cache-retention.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/prompt-cache-retention.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/extra-params.cache-retention-default.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/prompt-cache-retention.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/extra-params.cache-retention-default.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/amazon-bedrock/index.test.ts extensions/amazon-bedrock/stream.runtime.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo`\n\nLive Bedrock Nova request proof was not run because this Codex environment does not have AWS Bedrock credentials. Redacted live `Converse` or `ConverseStream` proof is still needed before merge.\n\nAI-assisted contribution.",
